#: Game.Levels.SubSpaces.L01_SubSpaces
msgid "We are going to begin by looking at the properties of a subspace. Suppose that V is a vector space over a field F and that W is a subset\n"
"of V . We say that W is a (vector) subspace of V if it is a vector space in its own\n"
"right with respect to vector addition and scalar multiplication inherited from V. Thus we will begin by looking at the importance of containing the zero vector."
msgstr ""

#: Game.Levels.DemoWorld.L01_HelloWorld
msgid "We are going to begin by looking at the usage of two of our exams to expand them\n"
"! The two axioms are add_zero: `вИА a :  F, a + 0 = a` and add_comm : вИА a b :  F , a + b = b + a.\n"
"Using these two axioms we want to expand upon add_zero to be in a more complete. What i mean by this\n"
"is that ater this level we will not only be able to say that a + 0 = a, but that 0+a =a."
msgstr ""

